This paper deals with word embeddings, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) tasks such as text classification, sentiment analysis, and machine translation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves optimization techniques and machine learning algorithms, which are relevant to categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses the evaluation of word embeddings, which is relevant to categories such as cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
